ition the Crypto.com ecosystem—including the Exchange, OTC desk, and Custody solutions—to meet the specific needs of institutional traders.\nOnboarding Management: Drive the end-to-end onboarding process, coordinating with Legal, Compliance, and Operations to ensure a seamless \"time-to-trade\" for new clients.\nRelationship Management: Serve as the primary point of contact for your book of business, ensuring high retention and identifying opportunities for upselling or cross-selling new products.\nMarket Insights: Provide \"boots on the ground\" feedback to the Product and Strategy teams regarding competitor pricing, feature gaps, and client pain points.\nSales Reporting: Maintain accurate records of sales activity and forecasts within the CRM, providing regular updates on KPIs such as Trading Volume and Assets under Management (AUM).\nJob Requirements\nLanguage: Native fluency in Arabic and Professional fluency in English\nExperience: 4–7 years of experience in Institutional Sales, Business Development, or Relationship Management within FinTech or Traditional Finance.\nDomain Knowledge: 2+ years of dedicated experience in the digital asset space, with a solid understanding of spot/derivatives trading and custodial workflows.\nNetwork: An existing network of institutional contacts (e.g., crypto-native funds, HFT firms, or asset managers) is highly preferred.\nTechnical Literacy: Ability to discuss API connectivity, FIX protocol, and sub-account structures with client technical teams.\nExecution Focus: A proven track record of meeting or exceeding individual sales quotas and volume targets.\nCommunication: Strong presentation skills with the ability to navigate complex conversations with Portfolio Managers and Operations Heads.\nAgility: A \"startup\" mindset with the ability to pivot quickly as market conditions and regulatory environments change.\nLife @ Crypto.com\n\nEmpowered to think big. Try new opportunities while working with a talented, ambitious and supportive team.\nTransformational and proactive working environment. Elevate employees to find thoughtful and innovative solutions.\nGrowth from within. We help to develop new skill-sets that would impact the shaping of your personal and professional growth.\nWork Culture. Our colleagues are some of the best in the industry; we are all here to help and support one another.\nOne cohesive team. Engage stakeholders to achieve our ultimate goal - Cryptocurrency in every wallet.\n\nAre you ready to kickstart your future with us?\n\nBenefits\n\nCompetitive salary\nMedical insurance package with extended coverage to dependents\nAttractive annual leave entitlement including: birthday, work anniversary\nWork Flexibility Adoption. Flexi-work hour and hybrid or remote set-up\nAspire career alternatives through us. Our internal mobility program can offer employees a diverse scope.\nWork Perks: crypto.com visa card provided upon joining\n\nOur Crypto.com benefits packages vary depending on region requirements, you can learn more from our talent acquisition team.\n\nAbout Crypto.com:\n\nFounded in 2016, Crypto.com serves more than 150 million customers and is the world's fastest growing global cryptocurrency platform. Our vision is simple: Cryptocurrency in Every Wallet™. Built on a foundation of security, privacy, and compliance, Crypto.com is committed to accelerating the adoption of cryptocurrency through innovation and empowering the next generation of builders, creators, and entrepreneurs to develop a fairer and more equitable digital ecosystem.\n\nLearn more at https://crypto.com.\n\nCrypto.com is an equal opportunities employer and we are committed to creating an environment where opportunities are presented to everyone in a fair and transparent way. Crypto.com values diversity and inclusion, seeking candidates with a variety of backgrounds, perspectives, and skills that complement and strengthen our team.\n\nPersonal data provided by applicants will be used for recruitment purposes only.\n\nPlease note that only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.\n\nWe may use artificial intelligence tools to analyze the content of your Resume/CV against the specific requirements for the position. The purpose is to support our recruitment team in reviewing applications more effectively. These tools assist our recruitment team in their evaluation of your application by providing recommendations, but they do not replace human judgment. Final hiring decisions are ultimately made by humans who consider the insights generated by the tools along with other relevant information. If you would like more details about how your personal information is processed, please contact us."}
{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=4d4ed712419dbc7d","title":"Head of Community","company":"Crypto Banter","location":"{\"city\":\"Remote\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Remote\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Remote\",\"latitude\":25,\"longitude\":-40,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":true,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"3 months ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=4d4ed712419dbc7d","description":"Why this role\nCrypto School is building a new model around short, high-intent trading challenges and live trading, instead of long, static courses.\nThese challenges live or die on the community experience:\nPeople need to feel welcomed and guided\nQuestions and issues need to be solved fast\nWins and stories need to be captured and fed back into marketing\n\nYour job is to be the face of the challenge community:\npart crypto community manager\npart customer issues point person\npart marketing partner who spots stories and signals before anyone else\n\nYou sit on the growth side of the business, not in a back-office support queue.\n\nWhat success looks like (first 3–6 months)\nEvery live challenge community feels alive, safe and supported - clear pinned info, daily touch points, fast answers.\nMost questions get a helpful reply within a few business hours, or are cleanly escalated with context.\nRepeated friction (KYC, deposits, rules confusion, access issues) is documented and fed back to Product / CRM / Growth so it gets fixed, not just answered.\nEach challenge produces real student wins and testimonials that hosts and marketing actually use.\n\nWhat you’ll do\n1) Community management\nRun the day-to-day community for each challenge:\n-welcome new members\n-post daily check ins and reminders\n-keep rules, FAQs and key links pinned and easy to find\n-Keep the vibe high energy but safe:\n-enforce rules\n-kill spam/scams\n-de-escalate when needed\nCoordinate with hosts and the growth team on:\n-kick off posts\n-live session announcements\n-final day wrap ups and celebrations\n-Use polls, questions and small prompts to get more people posting and sharing progress.\n\n2) Customer issues & support\nBe first line for questions on:\n-exchange sign up / KYC / deposits\n-challenge rules and daily tasks\n-access problems (links, logins, roles, etc.)\nTriage issues:\n-solve directly when you can\n-escalate cleanly with context when you cannot (to ops / product / CRM / support).\nMaintain and improve:\n-FAQs and “start here” posts\n-saved replies / macros for common issues\n-Track recurring friction and raise it with clear examples so the teams can remove it at the root.\n\n3) Marketing, stories and reactivation\nSpot wins and “aha” moments:\n-screenshots, PnL, progress posts, good quotes (with permission and proper disclaimers).\nPackage these for marketing and hosts:\n-short story write ups\n-testimonial snippets\n-ideas for case studies or social posts\n-Help run reactivation and referral pushes inside the community when we launch new challenges or offers.\n\n4) Simple reporting & feedback\nTrack basic community health per challenge:\n-joins vs active members\n-message volume\n-response times\n-top 5 issue categories\nAfter each challenge, write a short summary:\n-what worked\n-what broke\n-what you recommend changing next time\n\nRequirements\n2–4+ years in crypto / trading community management, customer success for a trading / fintech / edtech product, or a similar role.\nSolid working knowledge of crypto and exchanges:\nspot vs derivatives\nbasic leverage and margin concepts\nKYC / verification and deposit flowsYou do not need to be a pro trader, but you must be able to guide beginners safely and avoid reckless advice.\nReal experience running communities on Discord and/or Telegram (Nas.io, circle or similar is a plus).\nStrong written English:\n-explain complex things simply\n-stay calm and clear with upset users\n-keep a tone that fits Banter / Crypto School.\nExperience handling customer issues:\n-asking the right questions\n-documenting context\n-following through until the user is actually unblocked.\nMarketing centric mindset:\n-you see how community, support and lifecycle tie into the funnel\n-you naturally think “how do we turn this into a win, story or learning”.\n\nNice to have\nYou’ve traded yourself and know the emotional side of winning and losing.\nBasic Canva or similar skills to create simple visuals or announcement posts.\nExperience working with remote product, data and growth teams.\nComfortable occasionally working outside standard hours for live events or big challenge moments (with time off in lieu, not a 24/7 grind).\n\nWhy join us\nBe at the heart of a new challenge based trading education model, not just another Discord mod.\nSee your work directly impact user outcomes - fewer stuck users, more real success stories.\nSmall, fast team with real autonomy - you own the challenger community experience.\nMission driven environment focused on financial education, not just shilling coins.\n\nWe may use artificial intelligence (AI) tools to support parts of the hiring process, such as reviewing applications, analyzing resumes, or assessing responses. These tools assist our recruitment team but do not replace human judgment. Final hiring decisions are ultimately made by humans. If you would like more information about how your data is processed, please contact us."}
