{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=530ecce1caf37dae","title":"Zen Media Strategic Partnerships & Business Development Manager","company":"Optimum7","location":"{\"city\":\"Dubai\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Dubai\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Dubai\",\"latitude\":25.20485,\"longitude\":55.270782,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":false,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"3 months ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=530ecce1caf37dae","description":"Strategic Partnerships & Business Development Manager - MENA\n\nLocation: Remote, Dubai\n\nExperience Required: Minimum 5 years in business development, partnerships, channel sales, or strategic networking roles\n\nZen Media is the go-to B2B marketing and PR agency helping enterprise software, healthcare technology, professional services, and manufacturing brands achieve measurable growth and market leadership. By combining strategic content, leveraged media relations, and dynamic social amplification, we help our clients influence discerning buyers, shorten sales cycles, and drive ROI. Our work has been featured in leading publications such as Forbes, Fast Company, Ad Age, and The Wall Street Journal, and we have helped clients double their industry dominance and achieve profitable exits.\n\nRole Overview:\n\nWe are seeking a results-focused Strategic Partnerships & Business Development Manager (MENA) to build and strengthen Zen Media’’s partner ecosystem across the Middle East. This individual will identify, engage, and secure high-value partnerships with digital agencies, technology providers, B2B solution companies, consultants, and enterprise networks that can generate qualified opportunities and mutual growth.\n\nThis is a highly network-driven role, ideal for someone who excels in relationship building, communicates charismatically and professionally, and understands how to implement partnership strategies that lead to measurable revenue impact.\n\nWhat You’ll Do\n\nDevelop and execute partnership and business development strategies across the MENA region in alignment with company growth goals.\n\nBuild a strong pipeline of partnerships with agencies, SaaS companies, enterprise solution providers, technology platforms, and professional networks.\n\nProactively conduct networking, outreach, and relationship-building through events, associations, digital channels, and industry communities.\n\nRepresent Zen Media in the market as a knowledgeable, credible, and relationship-first growth partner.\n\nLead the full partnership lifecycle—prospecting, pitch, negotiation, onboarding, activation, and ongoing collaboration.\n\nMaintain timely and structured follow-up schedules to maximize alliance engagement and conversion.\n\nWork closely with marketing, sales, and executive leadership to develop joint strategies for co-marketing, lead sharing, and shared revenue models.\n\nTrack performance metrics, including partnership pipeline growth, conversions, revenue contribution, and engagement results.\n\nKeep an active pulse on the MENA market, competitive landscape, and opportunities for expansion.\n\nDeliver regular reporting and insights to internal leadership for strategic decision-making.\n\nWhat You Bring\n\nMinimum 5+ years of experience in business development, alliance management, channel sales, or partnership growth roles.\n\nStrong network-building abilities and proven experience developing strategic relationships in the MENA region.\n\nExceptional communication and stakeholder management skills—written, verbal, presentation, and negotiation.\n\nConfident and professional presence in events, meetings, networking settings, and digital interactions.\n\nTarget-driven mindset with the ability to independently manage pipelines, timelines, and objectives.\n\nExperience in B2B, digital marketing, SaaS, eCommerce, or related industries is a strong advantage.\n\nAbility to work autonomously, proactively, and remotely while collaborating with cross-functional teams.\n\nFluency in English required; Arabic is a plus.\n\nWhat’s Your Next Step?\n\nAt Zen Media, you’ll work with ambitious, high-growth B2B brands while collaborating with a brilliant team of strategists, creators, and PR experts. You’ll play a critical role in shaping the client experience and contributing directly to the success of our agency and the businesses we serve.\nIf you take pride in delivering white-glove service, staying hyper-organized, and keeping fast-paced projects on track, we want to hear from you.\n\nStill Unsure?\n\nIf you'd like to learn more about Zen Media before making your decision, we invite you to check out the links below:\n\nVisit our website: https://zenmedia.com/\n\nFollow us on LinkedIn: https://www.linkedin.com/company/wearezenmedia"}
{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=569219a002870814","title":"Head of Professional Services Sales - IBM Maximo / EAM Solutions","company":"MaxAccelerate","location":"{\"city\":\"Dubai\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Dubai\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Dubai\",\"latitude\":25.20485,\"longitude\":55.270782,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":false,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"2 months ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=569219a002870814","description":"Head of Professional Services Sales — IBM Maximo / EAM Solutions\n\nRemote (Global) | Relocation Sponsorship: Dubai option (Tax-Free Earnings)\nDepartment: Professional Services | Company: MaxAccelerate Technology Group\n\nAbout MaxAccelerate\n\nAt MaxAccelerate, we’re on a mission to bring the world of technology together — combining IBM Maximo, AI-driven data intelligence, and next-generation professional services into one powerful ecosystem.\n\nWe partner with some of the world’s largest enterprises and IBM Business Partners to deliver high-impact EAM solutions, digital transformations, supporting partners and our end clinets globally...\n\nThis is your chance to join a fast-growing global technology group, work with world-class teams, and help reshape how organizations manage and optimize their assets.\n\nAbout the Role\n\nWe’re looking for a Head of Professional Services Sales — a commercially driven leader with a deep understanding of enterprise consulting and a passion for customer success.\n\nIn this role, you’ll own the global sales strategy for our IBM Maximo and EAM professional services portfolio. You’ll build relationships with major enterprise clients, develop strategic partnerships, and lead high-value deals that transform how companies operate.\n\nThis isn’t a technical role — it’s about vision, relationships, and results. You’ll be the face of MaxAccelerate to the market: driving growth, inspiring clients, and shaping the future of EAM solutions worldwide.\n\nWhat You’ll Do\nLead the Professional Services sales strategy for IBM Maximo, MAS 9, and EAM transformation projects.\nIdentify and close new business opportunities across key industries (utilities, transport, manufacturing, government).\nBuild and nurture long-term client and partner relationships.\nDevelop proposals, lead negotiations, and secure multi-year service engagements.\nCollaborate closely with our delivery and marketing teams to align resources and go-to-market efforts.\nRepresent MaxAccelerate at industry events, IBM partner summits, and webinars.\nExpand adjacent service lines, including MAS upgrades, managed services, and AI-driven reporting (DataMax AI).\n\nWhat You’ll Bring\nProven track record in professional services or EAM sales, ideally with IBM Maximo or similar enterprise software.\nExperience in solution selling, enterprise consulting, or partner management.\nStrong commercial and negotiation skills with C-level clients.\nUnderstanding of Maximo / MAS 8–9 ecosystem, upgrades, and implementation lifecycles (advantageous).\nSelf-driven, entrepreneurial mindset — able to work remotely and deliver results.\nExcellent presentation and communication skills.\n\n✨ Why Join Us\nBe part of a global technology group transforming the EAM industry.\nWork with cutting-edge solutions including DataMax AI and IBM Maximo MAS 9.\nCollaborate with world-class consultants and AI specialists.\nRemote-first environment — work from anywhere.\nRelocation sponsorship to Dubai with tax-free earnings option.\nCompetitive base salary + up to 25% commission on closed deals.\nFast-track career growth within a high-performing international team.\n\nPerks\n\n✅ Competitive salary + uncapped commission\n✅ Remote / flexibility\n✅ Dubai sponsorship opportunity\n✅ Fast Track to own your own Business Unit with Share options.\n✅ Be part of a high-growth, AI-powered future\n\nReady to accelerate your career?\n\nJoin us and be part of a team that’s redefining the future of asset management, data, and AI.\n\nRequirements\n\n✅ Requirements Experience\nMinimum 5–7 years’ experience in enterprise professional services sales, ideally within IBM Maximo / EAM, ERP, or digital transformation domains.\nProven record of achieving or exceeding annual sales quotas in professional or consulting services.\nExperience working directly with or for IBM, IBM Business Partners, or within the Maximo ecosystem (strong advantage).\nDemonstrated success in building and managing C-level relationships across enterprise accounts.\nBackground in solution-based selling professional serives... (rather than product-only sales).\nExperience structuring and closing multi-year service contracts, SOWs, and framework agreements.\n\nKnowledge & Technical Understanding\nStrong working knowledge of IBM Maximo / MAS 8–9, or similar enterprise asset management (EAM) platforms.\nUnderstanding of EAM implementation lifecycles, upgrades, and managed services delivery models.\nKnowledge of enterprise IT environments (Azure, AWS, or IBM Cloud), service models, and client governance structures.\n\nSkills & Competencies\nExcellent communication, presentation, and negotiation skills.\nStrong commercial acumen with ability to build compelling business cases and ROI-driven proposals.\nStrategic thinker who can translate technical capability into customer value.\nConfident leading workshops, bids, and solution presentations.\nHigh level of organizational discipline and ability to manage multiple complex opportunities simultaneously.\nCollaborative leadership style — comfortable working across technical delivery, marketing, and partner teams.\n\nEducation & Certifications\nRequired: Bachelor’s degree in Business, Engineering, Computer Science, or related field.\nPreferred: MBA or postgraduate qualification.\nDesirable: IBM Maximo, ITIL, or cloud certifications (Azure / AWS / IBM).\n\nOther Requirements\nAbility to work independently in a remote, international environment.\nWillingness to travel occasionally for client meetings, conferences, or partner events.\nEligible to relocate to Dubai (company sponsorship available).\nFluent in English; additional languages are an advantage.\n\nBenefits\n\n✅ Competitive salary + uncapped commission up to 25% commission\n✅ Remote / hybrid flexibility\n✅ Dubai sponsorship opportunity\n✅ Access to global enterprise projects\n✅ Be part of a high-growth, AI-powered future"}
{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=5b38d3ef063855fd","title":"Senior Product Designer","company":"Careem","location":"{\"city\":\"Dubai\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Dubai\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Dubai\",\"latitude\":25.20485,\"longitude\":55.270782,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":false,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"12 days ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=5b38d3ef063855fd","description":"Careem is building the Everything App for the greater Middle East — making it easy to move around, order food and groceries, manage payments, and more. Our purpose is simple: to simplify and improve people’s lives and build an awesome organisation that inspires.\nSince 2012, Careem has enabled earnings for over 2.5 million Captains, simplified the lives of more than 70 million customers, and built a platform where the region’s best talent and entrepreneurs thrive. We operate in 70+ cities across 10 countries, from Morocco to Pakistan.\n\nWe’re now entering our next chapter — one powered by AI. We’re looking for AI talent: curious problem-solvers who know how to apply AI to build tools, automate workflows, and create real impact. Whether it’s streamlining operations, enhancing customer experience, or reimagining internal systems — we want people who can make Careem work smarter and move faster.\n\nAbout the Team\n\nThe Product Designer II - Design System at Careem is responsible for the development, implementation, and governance of the company's design system. This role ensures consistency, scalability, and user-centered experiences across all digital platforms. The Product Designer II - Design System will collaborate with cross-functional teams to define, maintain, and evolve design standards, guidelines, and components. This role requires expertise in design systems, stakeholder management, and strategic alignment with business objectives, while fostering innovation and mentorship.\n\nAbout the Role\n\nDesign System Evolution\nOversee the development and iterative refinement of Careem's design system, ensuring alignment with business goals and user requirements.\nEstablish and enforce scalable design standards, guidelines, and best practices to enhance consistency and user experience across all digital platforms.\nProvide expert guidance on design decisions within Careem's product ecosystem, influencing product strategy.\nArticulate and advocate for the value proposition of the design system, promoting efficiency, consistency, and quality throughout the organization.\nCollaboration and Stakeholder Engagement\nPartner with product management, engineering, and design teams to integrate design solutions with broader business strategies.\nManage stakeholder relationships, including executive leadership, to ensure clear communication, alignment on priorities, and transparency.\nLead design guilds to gather cross-product input and shape a viable, scalable design system.\nProcess and synthesize high volumes of feedback to refine system components and maintain alignment with stakeholder needs.\nComponent Ownership and System Implementation\nManage the full lifecycle of design system components, from conception to deployment and iteration, ensuring optimization for scalability and usability.\nDevelop and maintain comprehensive documentation for the design system, ensuring accessibility for product managers, designers, and engineers.\nCollaborate with engineering teams to translate design patterns into deployable components, ensuring technical feasibility and high-quality implementation.\nChampion accessibility best practices (WCAG) and collaborate with the digital accessibility team to ensure an inclusive design system.\nStrategic Product and Project Management\nAlign with product teams on the design system backlog and roadmap, balancing immediate functionality with long-term scalability.\nFacilitate decision-making to define the scope and timeline of implementation.\nProactively identify and drive system improvement initiatives that deliver high-impact outcomes for Careem.\nDriving Innovation and Continuous Improvement\nMonitor industry trends and introduce new patterns, tools, and design approaches.\nConduct regular design reviews and critique sessions to ensure the design system's quality, consistency, and utility.\nFoster an innovative mindset, pushing design boundaries while adhering to established standards.\nMentorship and Team Development\nFollow the visual direction for Careem, fostering a collaborative and high-performance culture.\nMentor team members and other designers, offering guidance on complex design challenges and skill development.\nInspire and motivate the team by setting a clear vision for design initiatives and supporting strategic alignment.\nCommunication and System Advocacy\nServe as the primary advocate for the design system within Careem, communicating its purpose and benefits to diverse audiences.\nGather feedback from design, product, and engineering teams for continuous system improvement.\nSynthesize stakeholder insights into actionable system enhancements, ensuring alignment with business objectives.\nQuality, Precision, and Thought Leadership\nEnsure design work reflects high accuracy, with comprehensive consideration and documentation of edge cases and potential risks.\nPromote simplification and unification of design patterns to manage complexity, justifying necessary exceptions.\nDevelop high-fidelity prototypes to facilitate informed business decisions.\nCross-Functional Influence and Strategic Vision\nRepresent the Design organization at Careem, advocating for design system initiatives and influencing executive-level decision-making.\nAlign design system processes with Careem's overarching vision, driving organizational change and promoting innovation.\nUtilize data, storytelling, and visual design skills to build consensus and inspire stakeholders at all levels.\n\nWhat we’ll provide you\n\nWe offer colleagues the opportunity to drive impact in the region while they learn and grow. As a full time Careem colleague, you will be able to:\n\nWork and learn from great minds by joining a community of inspiring colleagues.\nPut your passion to work in a purposeful organisation dedicated to creating impact in a region with a lot of untapped potential.\nExplore new opportunities to learn and grow every day.\nWork 4 days a week in office & 1 day from home, and remotely from any country in the world for 30 days a year with unlimited vacation days per year. (If you are in an individual contributor role in tech, you will have 2 office days a week and 3 to work from home.)\nAccess to healthcare benefits and fitness reimbursements for health activities including gym, health club, and training classes."}
{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=5c4e905df8816651","title":"Customer Success Manager- Hospitality Technology","company":"Reivernet Group of Companies","location":"{\"city\":null,\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"UAE\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"UAE\",\"latitude\":0,\"longitude\":0,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":false,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"4 days ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=5c4e905df8816651","description":"About Reivernet Group of Companies\n\nThe Reivernet Group of Companies is made up of seven entities: RN Projects, Reivernet, IT Triage, Site Compass, Stella (Bright Star), RN Gateway and RGC Management. We design, build, configure, support and document complex data networks for business, with a focus on hotel networks.\n\nHeadquartered in Australia we have employees on every continent. We encourage a collaborative and transparent work ethic where everyone can be heard and enjoy the support of likeminded professionals.\n\nWe have over 20 years’ experience focusing in managing complex networks and currently support over 900 hotels across 35 countries. Reivernet is proud to be endorsed by the five major global hotel brands including Marriott, Hilton and Accor.\n\nOur customer base reflects our focus to truly align to the brands, not the supply chains or ownership clusters. We are subject matter experts in being able to articulate the value of brand standard benefits to owners, operators, IT clusters, guests and our competitors.\n\nAbout the role\n\nCustomer Success Managers (CSM) are critical in protecting daily and monthly service fees levels and growing revenue for existing customer relationships with individual properties. CSMs achieve this by maintaining strong customer relationships, driving customer loyalty through onboarding, regular reviews and effective escalation management. Through their relationships at each property, they also identify opportunities to grow revenue from those properties. This role covers the MEA region and can be viewed as a remote position, however we do hold ad-hoc meetings in our Dubai based office in Internet City and you will be connecting with local and EU based colleagues.\n\nWhat you'll do\n\nDevelop and implement a relationship development and retention plan for a portfolio of customers with a Reivernet managed services contract\nOnboard new customers once a network install or upgrade has been delivered ensuring a smooth transition to Reivernet management of the customers' network\nExecute the renewals process for existing managed services contracts driving retention\nIdentify and qualify cross-sell opportunities to hand over to regional sales managers\nMonitor managed services support performance and proactively manage any issues and escalations\nUse your Commercial acumen to protect revenue and margin while balancing Capex and Opex to meet customer requirements\n\nQualifications\n\nCSMs are critical in ensuring that customers derive maximum value for Reivernet's services which leads to higher customer satisfaction, retention and growth. You will offer proven sales ability including strong negotiation skills, persuasive ability, relationship management and strong English communication skills. CSMs are advocates for the customer by being resourceful internally to resolve customer issues and ensure smooth transition to Reivernet or successful day 1 of an upgrade. CSMs appreciate the importance of retaining the brand coupled with the ability to balance the needs of Reivernet and the customers' site.\n\nAside from the above the following skills will be highly regarded:\n\nHospitality technology experience\nKnowledge of the Hotel sector in MEA\nPartner Management\nSpoken Arabic\n\nSalary\n\nAED 24000 to 30000 /month\n\nShould your application progress to our shortlist we will arrange an initial Teams call with our Recruitment team.\n\nIf that is successful our Exec team will look forward to meeting you face to face on 12th. March in Dubai.\n\nWe understand that not everyone may meet every aspect listed in our job postings. If you are passionate about this role and believe you have the skills and drive to succeed, we encourage you to apply. We value diverse experiences and perspectives, and we are committed to building an inclusive and supportive workplace. Your unique background and talents could be just what we need to grow and innovate together.\n\n You must be based in UAE to be considered for this position.\n\nThe pay range for this role is:\n24,000 - 30,000 AED per month(UAE)"}
{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=639a3536d1f056c4","title":"Head, Member Engagement and Experience - Middle East","company":"International Federation of Accountants","location":"{\"city\":\"Remote\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Remote\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Remote\",\"latitude\":25,\"longitude\":-40,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":true,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"2 months ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=639a3536d1f056c4","description":"INTERNATIONAL FEDERATION OF ACCOUNTANTS (IFAC)\nThe IFAC Member Value Proposition (MVP) is embedded into all of IFAC’s activities:\nIFAC, by connecting and uniting its members, makes the accountancy profession truly global.\nIFAC member organizations are champions of integrity and professional quality and proudly carry their membership as a badge of international recognition.\nIFAC and its members work together to shape the future of the profession through learning, innovation, a collective voice, and commitment to the public interest.\n\nIFAC has a global multi-location model to deliver value to member organizations around the world. We welcome applicants from around the globe to apply and contribute to our mission.\n\nIFAC welcomes applicants from all regions, and this role can be remote. For this role, the preferred candidate should be based in the Middle East region.\n\nPOSITION SUMMARY\nThe Head, Member Engagement and Experience (MEE), Middle East, plays a pivotal role in strengthening IFAC’s MVP across the region by adapting, delivering, and maximizing it for each member organization. The role focuses on building trusted, long-term partnerships and collaborating closely with member bodies and a broad range of strategic stakeholders, including regulatory authorities, central banks, supreme audit institutions, business associations, stock exchanges, academic institutions and other relevant institutions.\n\nThis position is responsible for ensuring consistent, proactive, and meaningful engagement with members throughout the region, including identifying and managing a strong regional pipeline of global volunteers. The ideal candidate brings an established professional network, strong credibility, and a proven ability to influence across diverse institutional environments.\n\nWorking in close coordination with the global MEE team, the Regional Head ensures alignment and consistency in service delivery while responding effectively to regional needs and priorities. The role reports to one of the Global Heads of Member Engagement and Experience (MEE).\n\nESSENTIAL DUTIES & RESPONSIBILITIES\nEssential duties and responsibilities include those that are set out below. Other duties may be assigned to meet business needs.\n\n Member Engagement and Experience\nCustomize, deliver, and continuously enhance the MVP for each member organization, strengthening the overall member experience across the Middle East.\nLeverage data, insights, and member feedback to understand, prioritize, and respond effectively to diverse member and jurisdictional needs. In turn, relay this information back into IFAC to support member’s fulfillment of IFAC membership requirements.\nSupport the development and execution of IFAC’s regional and jurisdictional member engagement strategies for The Middle East, fostering strong relationships, enhancing the overall member experience, advancing the MVP and driving measurable impact across the region.\nEngage proactively and consistently with members to build trust and collaborative relationships that support their strategic objectives.\nMonitor and assess regional developments impacting IFAC’s members, providing proactive insights and guidance to inform and shape IFAC’s strategic agenda.\nProvide advisory and advocacy support to members on legislative, regulatory, and public policy matters impacting the profession.\nCollaborate closely with the Global MEE team to ensure alignment and consistency in service delivery worldwide.\nAct as a visible role model and champion of the MVP, upholding IFAC’s commitment to integrity, professional quality, and public interest.\n\n Stakeholder Engagement\nBuild, maintain, and deepen strong relationships with a broad range of internal and external stakeholders.\nServe as a trusted advisor to Professional Accountancy Organizations (PAOs) and other key stakeholders across the region.\nWork with organizations who have expressed interest in membership with IFAC on the IFAC membership requirements and collaborate internally to adhere to established processes around membership applications.\nWork collaboratively with regional bodies to advance shared objectives.\nConnect, engage, and collaborate with diverse stakeholders, including national governments, financial and tax regulators, independent audit oversight authorities, central banks, stock exchanges, corporate governance institutes, universities, supreme audit institutions, and business associations.\nIdentify, engage, and manage potential volunteers across the region to contribute to IFAC’s global volunteer pipeline.\n\nEvent Coordination and Representation\nFacilitate knowledge-sharing, advocacy, and collaboration among PAOs, policymakers, regulators, and government bodies at national and regional levels.\nPlan, deliver, and evaluate regional events, forums, and workshops, ensuring alignment with the MVP and IFAC’s strategic objectives.\nAt the discretion of the CEO and Global Head, MEE, represent IFAC at high-level meetings, forums, and professional events, enhancing organizational visibility, influence, and stakeholder relationships.\nWill include travel within the Middle East and abroad.\n\nQUALIFICATIONS & REQUIRED SKILLS\nBachelor’s degree or an equivalent in Business, Accounting, International Relations, Public Policy, or a related field, preferred.\n5+ years or relevant experience in member engagement, stakeholder relations, public affairs, or leadership roles within professional or member-based organizations, preferred.\nStrong communication skills, both written and oral, paired with excellent active listening abilities.\nFluency in English and Arabic is required; proficiency in other languages is appreciated.\nProven capability to manage multiple priorities, work independently, and deliver results in a dynamic, fast-paced environment.\nStrong understanding of regional trends and issues affecting the accountancy profession, with the ability to translate insight into action.\nExperience in data collection and analysis, including tracking trends, measuring impact, and generating actionable insights.\nPractical experience using Microsoft Dynamics Customer Relationship Management (CRM) systems.\nStrong project management skills, creativity, and adaptability in response to shifting priorities.\nProactive, forward-looking approach and commitment to the public interest.\nAbility to identify and execute opportunities to enhance the MVP, while navigating cultural and jurisdictional sensitivities.\nCollaborative team orientation with the ability to work effectively across multiple cultures and organizational levels.\nStrong interpersonal skills, diplomacy, and gravitas to build consensus among diverse perspectives.\nWillingness to travel within the Middle East with the potential for some international travel.\n\nPrimary Location: The Middle East\n\nIFAC is an equal employment employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, age, disability or protected veteran status, or any other legally protected basis, in accordance with applicable law.\nYL32qWoCPS"}
{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=66a33af47bebb068","title":"Head of Organic Growth","company":"Revolut","location":"{\"city\":\"Remote\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Remote\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Remote\",\"latitude\":25,\"longitude\":-40,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":true,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"12 days ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=66a33af47bebb068","description":"About Revolut\n\nPeople deserve more from their money. More visibility, more control, and more freedom. Since 2015, Revolut has been on a mission to deliver just that. Our powerhouse of products — including spending, saving, investing, exchanging, travelling, and more — help our 70+ million customers get more from their money every day.\n\nAs we continue our lightning-fast growth,‌ 2 things are essential to our success: our people and our culture. In recognition of our outstanding employee experience, we've been certified as a Great Place to Work™. So far, we have 13,000+ people working around the world, from our offices and remotely, to help us achieve our mission. And we're looking for more brilliant people. People who love building great products, redefining success, and turning the complexity of a chaotic world into the simplicity of a beautiful solution.\n\nAbout the role\n\nGrowth at Revolut is where strategy, data, and creativity come together. The team drives expansion by launching in new markets, accelerating acquisition, and boosting engagement and retention. They turn insights into action, working across teams and channels to scale what works and experiment with what’s next.\n\nWe're looking for a Head of Organic Growth to drive organic acquisition and conversion for Revolut Business globally. As a member of our management team, you'll own strategy and execution for organic funnel performance.\n\nYou'll ensure Revolut Business is discoverable, accurately described, and competitively positioned using SEO and GEO operating systems.\n\nUp to shape what's next in finance? Let's get in touch.\n\nWhat you'll be doing\n\nRecruiting, coaching, and developing an Organic Growth team, and managing freelancers where needed\nRunning weekly operating routines, including performance reviews, content pipeline, tech SEO backlog\nMonitoring and optimising visibility in LLM answers or AI search results to identify coverage gaps, create or refresh authoritative sources, and improve entity clarity where relevant\nPartnering with Web and Engineering teams to ship technical SEO improvements\nDriving content planning and production, including funnel pages, landing pages, comparison pages, and use-cases, to maintain quality and conversion intent\nLeading link acquisition initiatives to build authority and rankings\nSetting-up measurement and attribution views for organic impact\n\nWhat you'll need\n\n8+ years organic growth or SEO experience in high-growth environments, such as SaaS or fintech\nA track record of scaling organic acquisitions with ownership of business outcomes\nExpertise in SEO, including keyword research, on-page, technical SEO, and link building\nThe ability to work with engineers and ship technical change\nA data-driven mindset, and to be comfortable with attribution/tooling discussions\nExcellent cross-functional leadership and ownership to succeed in a high-performance environment\n\nNice to have\n\nFamiliarity with international or multi-market SEO, including localisation workflows and multi-language content\nKnowledge of programmatic SEO and scaled landing-page generation\nExperience in fintech, payments, or SME banking\n\nCompensation range\n\nKrakow: PLN33,000 - PLN36,600 gross monthly*\nPoland: PLN33,000 - PLN36,600 gross monthly*\nOther locations: Compensation will be discussed during the interview process\n\n*Final compensation will be determined based on the candidate's qualifications, skills, and previous experience\n\nBuilding a global financial super app isn’t enough. Our Revoluters are a priority, and that’s why in 2021 we launched our inaugural D&I Framework, designed to help us thrive and grow everyday. We're not just doing this because it's the right thing to do. We’re doing it because we know that seeking out diverse talent and creating an inclusive workplace is the way to create exceptional, innovative products and services for our customers. That’s why we encourage applications from people with diverse backgrounds and experiences to join this multicultural, hard-working team.\n\nImportant notice for candidates:\n\nJob scams are on the rise. Please keep these guidelines in mind when applying for any open roles.\n\n• Only apply through official Revolut channels. We don’t use any third-party services or platforms for our recruitment.\n\n• Always double-check the emails you receive. Make sure all communications are being done through official Revolut emails, with an @revolut.com domain.\n\nWe won't ask for payment or personal financial information during the hiring process. If anyone does ask you for this, it’s a scam. Report it immediately.\n\nBy submitting this application, I confirm that all the information given by me in this application for employment and any additional documents attached hereto are true to the best of my knowledge and that I have not wilfully suppressed any material fact. I confirm I have disclosed if applicable any previous employment with Revolut. I accept that if any of the information given by me in this application is in any way false or incorrect, my application may be rejected, any offer of employment may be withdrawn or my employment with Revolut may be terminated summarily or I may be dismissed. By submitting this application, I agree that my personal data will be processed in accordance with Revolut's Candidate Privacy Notice\n\nNotice: This is a remote position based in United Arab Emirates."}
{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=699612d1bd4b6318","title":"Business Operations Manager","company":"Trivium","location":"{\"city\":\"Dubai\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Dubai\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Dubai\",\"latitude\":25.20485,\"longitude\":55.270782,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":false,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"8 days ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=699612d1bd4b6318","description":"Operations Manager\n\nCompany: Bloom & Bond\nEmployment Type: Full-Time\nCompensation: $50,000 – $70,000 per year (based on experience)\nLocation: Remote (must be comfortable working across multiple time zones)\n\nAbout Bloom & Bond\n\nBloom & Bond is a fast-growing e-commerce / DTC brand building a scalable, systems-driven business designed for long-term growth. We operate lean, move quickly, and believe operational excellence is the foundation of scale.\n\nWe are not looking for an administrator.\nWe are hiring an operator.\n\nThis role is for someone who thrives on building structure, documenting processes, managing people, and ensuring nothing falls through the cracks. You will be responsible for turning complexity into clarity and building the operational backbone that supports sustainable growth.\n\nRole Overview\n\nThe Operations Manager will run the day-to-day operations of Bloom & Bond across systems, people, and supply chain.\n\nYou will:\n\nBuild and maintain operational systems\nHold the team accountable to KPIs\nOversee hiring and onboarding processes\nManage inventory, 3PL, and logistics\nProvide financial visibility into operational spend\n\nYour success will be measured by how well the business runs without friction, bottlenecks, or chaos.\n\nThis is a high-ownership role with direct impact on performance and scalability.\n\nCore Responsibilities1. Systems & SOP Development\nBuild, document, and maintain SOPs for every role and process inside Notion\nEnsure every team member has a clear playbook and job scorecard\nAudit current workflows and identify bottlenecks\nCreate systems that remove reliance on tribal knowledge\nMaintain operational dashboards and KPI trackers\nUse AI tools to automate and optimize repetitive processes\n2. People Management & Accountability\nServe as the primary day-to-day point of contact for the team\nRun weekly team standups and structured 1:1 meetings\nTrack KPIs using role-based scorecards\nConduct monthly and quarterly performance reviews\nLead underperformance conversations and manage PIPs when needed\nProcess contractor and team payments accurately and on time\nFoster a culture of accountability and ownership\n3. Hiring & Onboarding\nManage the hiring pipeline when new roles open (job posting, screening, assessments, scheduling)\nOversee recruiter (if/when added to the team)\nMaintain updated job descriptions and role scorecards\nBuild structured onboarding plans for every new hire\nEnsure new team members can ramp quickly using documented systems\n4. Supply Chain & Fulfillment\nOwn inventory tracking and demand forecasting\nProactively manage reorder cycles\nCoordinate freight logistics and shipment timelines\nManage 3PL relationships and monitor SLAs\nPrevent stockouts and overstock through forecasting accuracy\nContinuously optimize supply chain costs and efficiency\n5. Cost Visibility & Financial Oversight\nTrack recurring operational expenses (tools, subscriptions, vendors)\nIdentify anomalies and unnecessary spend\nDeliver a monthly OPEX summary with observations\nMonitor budget vs. actuals and flag discrepancies\nSupport data-driven operational decision-making\n\nRequirements\n\nRequirements\n2+ years in Operations or Project Management within e-commerce or DTC\nAdvanced Notion and/or ClickUp user (required)\nActively uses AI tools daily to build systems and automate workflows\nExperience managing remote teams across time zones\nHands-on supply chain experience (inventory, 3PL, freight, forecasting)\nComfortable reading and interpreting basic financial reports\nExperience managing hiring pipelines\nPreferred Experience\nScaling a DTC brand from early growth to structured operations\nBuilding KPI dashboards and operational scorecards\nImplementing automation using AI tools\nMulti-vendor and multi-channel supply chain exposure\n\nBenefits\n\nCompany: Bloom & Bond\nEmployment Type: Full-Time\nCompensation: $50,000 – $70,000 per year (based on experience)\nLocation: Remote (must be comfortable working across multiple time zones)"}
