ired Skills*\n\n* Strong portfolio demonstrating UI/UX projects.\n* Proficiency in *Figma, Adobe XD, Sketch, Photoshop, Illustrator*.\n* Knowledge of *HTML, CSS, and responsive design principles*.\n* Experience with *Design Systems & Accessibility (WCAG)*.\n* Understanding of *User Research & Usability Testing*.\n* Excellent communication and presentation skills.\n\n*Preferred Qualifications*\n\n* Experience with *mobile app design (iOS & Android)*.\n* Familiarity with *interaction design and micro-animations*.\n* Experience working in *Agile/Scrum environments*.\n* Bachelor’s degree in Design, Computer Science, or related field.\n\nJob Type: Full-time\n\nPay: AED7,000.00 - AED8,000.00 per month"}
{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=6ff2077bed88d21a","title":"Product Manager II","company":"Careem","location":"{\"city\":\"Dubai\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Dubai\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Dubai\",\"latitude\":25.20485,\"longitude\":55.270782,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":false,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"9 days ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=6ff2077bed88d21a","description":"Careem is building the Everything App for the greater Middle East — making it easy to move around, order food and groceries, manage payments, and more. Our purpose is simple: to simplify and improve people’s lives and build an awesome organisation that inspires.\nSince 2012, Careem has enabled earnings for over 2.5 million Captains, simplified the lives of more than 70 million customers, and built a platform where the region’s best talent and entrepreneurs thrive. We operate in 70+ cities across 10 countries, from Morocco to Pakistan.\n\nWe’re now entering our next chapter — one powered by AI. We’re looking for AI talent: curious problem-solvers who know how to apply AI to build tools, automate workflows, and create real impact. Whether it’s streamlining operations, enhancing customer experience, or reimagining internal systems — we want people who can make Careem work smarter and move faster.\n\nAbout the Team\n\nYou will join Careem's New Ventures team - the launchpad for our next big bets. It's where bold ideas become real businesses that move our region forward. Careem Box is our courier and parcel delivery product, operating across the UAE and Jordan. We're a small, entrepreneurial team that moves fast, takes ownership, and obsesses over building a product that genuinely simplifies life for our customers. If you thrive in a startup-within-a-startup environment, this is your place.\n\nAbout the Role\n\nWe're looking for a Product Manager II to own the product vision, roadmap, and execution for Careem Box across the UAE and Jordan. This is a high-ownership, high-ambiguity role - you won't just ship features, you'll define what gets built and why, partnering closely with Growth, Commercial, Finance, and Operations to drive meaningful business outcomes. You'll be the connective tissue between customer needs and business performance, setting the product direction for one of Careem's most exciting bets.\n\nWhat you'll do\n\nOwn the product roadmap and long-term strategy for Careem Box, making clear prioritization calls that balance customer value with commercial impact.\nNavigate complex dependencies across the Careem super app, aligning multiple product areas to deliver a seamless customer experience.\nLead cross-functional product initiatives, partnering with Growth, Commercial, Finance, and Operations teams across UAE and Jordan to ship impactful capabilities end-to-end.\nDrive measurable business outcomes, using data and customer insights to identify opportunities, run experiments, and continuously improve key metrics across the Box experience.\nChampion the customer, deeply understanding the needs of senders and recipients to build a product that is reliable, intuitive, and genuinely saving the day!\nOperate with founder-level ownership, moving fast, removing blockers, and doing what it takes to make Box succeed in the market.\n\nWhat you'll need\n\n4–6 years of product management experience, ideally in customer-facing applications and/or mobility or logistics products.\nAn entrepreneurial mindset - energised by ambiguity, comfortable building from scratch, and taking full ownership of outcomes, not just outputs.\nStrong data proficiency with the ability to extract insights, validate hypotheses, and make evidence-based decisions. SQL experience is a plus.\nExceptional stakeholder management skills - able to align cross-functional teams around a shared vision and influence without authority.\nDeep customer obsession - you design with empathy and hold a high bar for the experiences you ship.\nA go-getter attitude - driven, resourceful, and ready to roll up your sleeves to get things done, no matter what stands in the way.\nComfort leveraging modern tools and AI to move faster and work smarter.\n\nWhat we’ll provide you\n\nWe offer colleagues the opportunity to drive impact in the region while they learn and grow. As a full time Careem colleague, you will be able to:\n\nWork and learn from great minds by joining a community of inspiring colleagues.\nPut your passion to work in a purposeful organisation dedicated to creating impact in a region with a lot of untapped potential.\nExplore new opportunities to learn and grow every day.\nWork 4 days a week in office & 1 day from home, and remotely from any country in the world for 30 days a year with unlimited vacation days per year. (If you are in an individual contributor role in tech, you will have 2 office days a week and 3 to work from home.)\nAccess to healthcare benefits and fitness reimbursements for health activities including gym, health club, and training classes."}
{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=704a095e58effe47","title":"Head of Research","company":"Revolut","location":"{\"city\":\"Remote\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Remote\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Remote\",\"latitude\":25,\"longitude\":-40,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":true,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"3 months ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=704a095e58effe47","description":"About Revolut\n\nPeople deserve more from their money. More visibility, more control, and more freedom. Since 2015, Revolut has been on a mission to deliver just that. Our powerhouse of products — including spending, saving, investing, exchanging, travelling, and more — help our 70+ million customers get more from their money every day.\n\nAs we continue our lightning-fast growth,‌ 2 things are essential to our success: our people and our culture. In recognition of our outstanding employee experience, we've been certified as a Great Place to Work™. So far, we have 13,000+ people working around the world, from our offices and remotely, to help us achieve our mission. And we're looking for more brilliant people. People who love building great products, redefining success, and turning the complexity of a chaotic world into the simplicity of a beautiful solution.\n\nAbout the role\n\nGrowth at Revolut is where strategy, data, and creativity come together. The team drives expansion by launching in new markets, accelerating acquisition, and boosting engagement and retention. They turn insights into action, working across teams and channels to scale what works and experiment with what’s next.\n\nWe're looking for a Head of Research to play a pivotal role in shaping our understanding of consumer needs, market trends, and competitive dynamics. Your insights will directly influence product positioning, market strategy, and campaign development, ensuring that every move we make is backed by rigorous research and a deep understanding of our customers.\n\nUp to turn data into impactful decisions and help scale a global fintech? Let's get in touch.\n\nWhat you'll be doing\n\nSupporting brand tracking and consumer research programmes across key markets\nDesigning and implementing high-quality surveys tailored to campaign and brand insight needs\nPartnering with Marketing Managers to ensure research effectively supports campaign planning and measurement\nAssisting in managing survey panels, ensuring data quality and timely delivery\nOrganising and executing ad hoc research requests and stakeholder briefs\nIntegrating research data into dashboards and analytic workflows\n\nWhat you'll need\n\nProven experience in market research, consumer insights, or a similar analytical role, preferably within a high-growth or tech-driven environment\nSolid knowledge of both quantitative and qualitative research methods, with hands-on experience in survey design and data analysis\nFamiliarity with brand tracking tools, survey platforms, and panel management\nThe ability to translate research findings into actionable insights that support marketing strategies and campaign performance\nExcellent communication and collaboration skills, with experience working cross-functionally with marketing, product, or data teams\nImpeccable attention to detail and organisational skills, with the ability to manage multiple projects and meet tight deadlines\nExperience with data visualisation tools (e.g., Tableau, Looker) and a basic understanding of analytic workflows\nA proactive mindset, curiosity, and a passion for understanding customer behaviour and brand performance\n\nCompensation range\n\nKrakow: PLN24,700 - PLN29,100 gross monthly*\nPoland: PLN24,700 - PLN29,100 gross monthly*\nOther locations: Compensation will be discussed during the interview process\n\n*Final compensation will be determined based on the candidate's qualifications, skills, and previous experience\