{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=987fd12a37bb6aea","title":"Business Development Representative","company":"Nebius","location":"{\"city\":\"Dubai\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Dubai\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Dubai\",\"latitude\":25.20485,\"longitude\":55.270782,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":false,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"17 days ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=987fd12a37bb6aea","description":"Why work at Nebius\nNebius is leading a new era in cloud computing to serve the global AI economy. We create the tools and resources our customers need to solve real-world challenges and transform industries, without massive infrastructure costs or the need to build large in-house AI/ML teams. Our employees work at the cutting edge of AI cloud infrastructure alongside some of the most experienced and innovative leaders and engineers in the field.\n\nWhere we work\nHeadquartered in Amsterdam and listed on Nasdaq, Nebius has a global footprint with R&D hubs across Europe, North America, and Israel. The team of over 800 employees includes more than 400 highly skilled engineers with deep expertise across hardware and software engineering, as well as an in-house AI R&D team.\n\nThe role\n\nWe’re looking for a Business Development Representative, who will be the first point of contact for leading companies across UAE and Saudi Arabia, exploring next-generation cloud and AI solutions. Working closely with Account Executives, Marketing, and Product teams, you will build and qualify pipeline to accelerate Nebius’s growth in Middle East and Africa markets.\n\nYou’re welcome to work remote from Dubai.\n\nYour responsibilities will include:\n\nTerritory & Account Penetration\n\nCollaborate with AEs to map and prioritize target accounts across Middle East and Africa, then execute a mix of outbound calls, personalized emails, and LinkedIn outreach to secure qualified meetings.\n\nInbound Lead Qualification\n\nScreen and qualify inbound MQLs generated by Marketing, ensuring each prospect meets BANT criteria before handing off a detailed prospect brief to AEs.\n\nCustomer & Market Engagement\n\nConduct qualification calls to uncover customer pain points, technical requirements, and budget.\nRepresent Nebius at key Middle East and Africa tech events, book on-site meetings, and follow up to maximize ROI.\n\nFeedback & Continuous Improvement\n\nGather market intelligence (common objections, competitive insights, feature requests) during prospect conversations and share it with Product and Marketing.\nMonitor outreach metrics—open rates, reply rates, connect rates—and collaborate with Sales Ops to optimize cadences and scripts.\nStay up to date on AI and cloud trends (e.g., generative AI in pharma R&D) to position Nebius’s value proposition effectively.\n\nWe expect you to have:\n\nLanguage & Market Expertise:\n\nFluent English and Arabic is required, both written and verbal.\n2+ years of SDR/BDR experience in cloud, B2B SaaS, or AI, with a proven track record targeting UAE and Middle East and Africa markets.\n\nTechnical & Sales Skills:\n\nStrong understanding of GDPR and local data-privacy regulations.\n\nSoft Skills & Mindset:\n\nHighly self-motivated, goal-oriented, and able to thrive in a fast-paced startup environment.\nExcellent written and verbal communication skills, with strong cross-cultural awareness and adaptability.\nCollaborative team player comfortable operating in a hybrid office model.\n\nIt will be an added bonus if you have:\n\n Familiarity with HubSpot CRM and sales engagement tools such as Outreach.\n\nWhat we offer\n\nCompetitive salary and comprehensive benefits package.\nOpportunities for professional growth within Nebius.\nFlexible working arrangements.\nA dynamic and collaborative work environment that values initiative and innovation.\n\nWe’re growing and expanding our products every day. If you’re up to the challenge and are excited about AI and ML as much as we are, join us!"}
{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=9a7399f7c3fbc4f6","title":"Associate Director Project Management (Residential)","company":"AtkinsRéalis","location":"{\"city\":\"Abu Dhabi\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Abu Dhabi\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Abu Dhabi\",\"latitude\":24.46,\"longitude\":54.36,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":false,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"25 days ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=9a7399f7c3fbc4f6","description":"Overview\n\nAs Associate Director, you will be responsible for leading and managing the project or projects within the Masterplan program through the project lifecycle. Work closely with our clients, design consultants, Construction supervision consultant, contractors and other stakeholders to ensure the projects objectives are met in line with our client requirements and expectations.\n\nWith a Strong background in construction management to manage and assist Construction supervision and Contractors meet project and client objectives.\n\nKnowledge of Modern Methods of Construction (MCC) with pre-cast fabrication being consider for the Villa is preferrable.\n\nWill be client facing and assist the Client Senior Manager Delivery ensuring the delivery of the Project though the project life cycle.\n\nYou will assist the Programme Director and support Senior Project Manager in ensuring that our scope of works is delivered to AtkinsRéalis and client's'expectations.\n\nYour role\n\nProgramme Delivery & Integration\n\nSupport the Project Director in ensuring consistent PMC delivery across villa and infrastructure packages.\nLead risk management, escalation, and resolution of issues impacting multiple packages or disciplines.\nMonitor interface between design, construction, and commercial teams to ensure delivery cohesion.\nEnsure compliance with delegated responsibilities under FIDIC where PMC is the named Engineer (site supervision delegated to CSC)\nTechnical understanding of multidisciplinary design (architecture, infrastructure, MEP, landscape)\n\nStakeholder & Authority Coordination\n\nManage relationships with the Client and key Abu Dhabi authorities (e.g., ADM, DMT, ITC, ADDC).\nCoordinate technical and administrative interfaces across contractors, consultants, and asset owners.\nEnsure MoU-driven authority engagements are fulfilled per programme and package timelines.\n\nCommercial & Governance Alignment\n\nLiaise with PMC Commercial and Controls teams to ensure risk, cost, and programme data are consistent and accurate.\nOversee PMC contributions to claims, variations, payment recommendations, and cost reporting.\nMaintain adherence to Client governance and escalation protocols.\n\nReporting & Communication\n\nSupport programme-wide reporting activities, including milestone performance, design coordination, and contractor progress.\nPrepare executive-level briefings and risk registers for Client leadership.\n\nGeneral\n\nAbility to lead cross-functional teams and drive timely resolution of complex design and construction challenges.\nDemonstrated leadership and people management skills, with the ability to motivate and engage team members to foster a positive and collaborative work environment.\nEffective communication and collaboration skills, both as a team player and as an independent contributor, with a demonstrated ability to balance teamwork and independent project assignments.\nProven track record in managing complex projects, displaying exemplary project management skills such as organization, time management, resourcefulness, flexibility, and communication.\nAbility to manage project timelines meticulously.\nStrong financial acumen and demonstrated attention to best value for investment within agreed budgets, ensuring cost-effective design solutions without compromising quality.\nResults-driven mindset, consistently achieving project goals and driving success in design delivery.\nEnsure AtkinsRéalis processes, forms and deliverables are followed, and when required, client processes and forms as applicable in full consultation with the client.\nManage, direct, lead and administrate the contracts of the various entities on the Program:\nLead Design Consultant (LDC)\nOther consultants appointed by the client.\nConstruction Supervision Consultant (CSC)\nEarly Works and Main Work Contractors\nShall coordinate and assist activities and work with various entities on the program:\nStakeholders not limited to: Client teams, tenants, facility management, operators etc.\nConsultants and Contractors\nStatutory Authorities with support of Stakeholder Manager\nConstruction Supervision Consultant (CSC)\nLogistics with support of logistics officer and assisted by client.\nManage and assist the client with the procurement of Design Consultant, specialists and Contractors as and when required.\nOverall awareness of PMC scope of services to manage and assist with, but not limited to:\nConstruction Management\nConstructability\nSafety in Design\nAssist in Change Management of the Project with the Cost and Commercial Teams, implement required change control processes, review and recommendation for Client confirmation.\nAssist and coordinate value management during the Design and construction stages in support of the Client.\nDetermine and manage risks that may affect the programme/project not limited to schedule, budget, client requirements, quality, constructability and compliance.\nAssist on monitoring and managing the Design and construction schedule with Project Controls and LDC\nAssist in Stakeholder Management: Develop the statutory approval workflow chart for all design stages and in alignment with Client and Statutory Authority approval requirements.\nOversee preparation of all technical documentation required for construction tender packages.\nPerform other duties as assigned.\nAbout you\n\nQualifications\n\nBachelor's degree in architecture, Civil Engineering, or relevant design discipline; Chartered status (e.g., RIBA, P. Eng, C. Eng) preferred.\nAble to work in a team environment and be client facing.\nActive leadership style.\n\nExperience\n\n20-25 years working experience with experience in the region preferrable.\nWith 10+ years' experience in UAE in design manager experience on hospitality projects.\nPreferable 5+ years in Project Management Consultancy.\nPost-Contract experience mainly with both Pre - Post Contract preferrable.\n\nCompetencies\n\nDeep knowledge of FIDIC contract implementation (including delegated site roles).\nExcellent stakeholder engagement and risk management capabilities.\nProven authority coordination and PMC delivery experience.\nStrong cross-functional leadership and commercial awareness.\nRewards & benefits\n\nExplore the rewards and benefits that help you thrive – at every stage of your life and your career.\n\nThis includes:\n\nTax-free salary.\nComprehensive life insurance coverage.\nPremium medical insurance for you and your dependents.\nGenerous annual leave balance.\nFlexible and hybrid work solutions.\nRemote work opportunities outside of country.\nCompany gratuity scheme.\nDiscretionary bonus program.\nAnnual flight contribution.\nRelocation assistance.\nTransportation & housing allowances (available for remote work locations).\nEmployee Wellbeing Program: 24/7 access to specialists in finance, legal matters, family care, personal health, fitness, and nutrition.\n\nSeize every opportunity to sharpen your skills, expand your expertise, and be recognized for the impact you make.\n\nAbout AtkinsRéalis\n\nWe're AtkinsRéalis, a world-class engineering services and nuclear organization. We connect people, data and technology to transform the world's'infrastructure and energy systems. Together, with our industry partners and clients, and our global team of consultants, designers, engineers and project managers, we can change the world. We're committed to leading our clients across our various end markets to engineer a better future for our planet and its people.\n\n#HC #ProjectLeadership #AtkinsRealis"}
