tionships with existing customers;Articulate client feedback and gaps in service/product offerings to continuously improve product features and customer satisfaction.Job RequirementsBachelor's degree or above;Solid experience in the crypto industry with a network of clients;Proven track record of meeting and exceeding sales targets;At least 2 years of prior sales experience in the financial services industry, preferably coming from an traditional exchange, 3rd party vendor working with buy-side trading clients or experience at crypto exchanges, lenders, custodians, or platform providers;Passionate for crypto finance and an expert understanding of cryptocurrency assets, derivatives, and trading workflows;Excellent communication, negotiation, and presentation skills;Ability to thrive in a dynamic and fast-paced environment;Fluency in both Mandarin Chinese and English is required. Proficiency in additional local languages is preferred.By submitting a job application, you confirm that you have read and agree to our Candidate Privacy Policy. &lt;https://www.matrixport.com/privacy-candidate&gt;"}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4368097771","title":"Business Development Manager - Medical Devices","company":"Taevas Life Sciences","location":"Hyderabad","remote":false,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"","description":"Candidate should be a licensed pharmacist in UAETitle : Sales / Business Development Manager ( Product Sales)Location : UAEEducation : Bachelor's in PharmacyKey Responsibilities:Primary Responsibility: Medical Device Sales and Commercialization StrategySales Strategy &amp; Implementation:Develop and execute a comprehensive commercialization strategy for assigned medical devices.Identify target markets, customer segments, and potential partnerships in the healthcare ecosystem.Conduct product demos and training for healthcare professionals, including doctors, hospital staff, and distributors.Market Expansion:Build relationships with hospitals/clinics/therapy centers, and distributors to expand the market presence.Identify growth opportunities through market research, key opinion leader (KOL) engagement, and competitor analysis.Sales Targets &amp; Performance:Achieve quarterly and annual sales targets for assigned products.Track and report key performance indicators (KPIs), including sales performance, client feedback, and competitor activities.Cross-functional Collaboration:Collaborate with regulatory, marketing, and operations teams to ensure compliance and alignment with customer needs.Coordinate post-sale support to ensure customer satisfaction and retention.Secondary Responsibility: Service Sales (Legal &amp; Regulatory Services)Promote and sell complementary services, such as legal representation services/Marketing Authorization Holder (MAH) services.Create and present service proposals tailored to client needs.Provide ongoing support to clients with service-related queries and ensure seamless service delivery.Additional Responsibility: Country Head FunctionsStrategic Leadership:Represent the company in the designated country or region, ensuring alignment with global business objectives.Develop and execute country-specific strategies for sales, marketing, and business development.Team Management:Build, manage, and lead a high-performing sales and operations team to achieve business objectives.Provide mentorship, training, and performance feedback to team members.Compliance &amp; Risk Management:Ensure all business activities comply with local regulatory and legal requirements.Mitigate risks associated with product sales, service delivery, and external partnerships.Stakeholder Engagement:Act as the primary point of contact for high-value customers, healthcare organizations, and governmental bodies.Cultivate relationships with key opinion leaders (KOLs) to enhance market credibility and visibility.Financial Oversight:Monitor the country’s P&amp;L (Profit and Loss) performance, managing budgets and allocating resources effectively.Identify cost-saving measures without compromising service quality or operational efficiency.Business Growth:Identify opportunities for new product launches and service expansions in the region.Collaborate with global teams to adapt strategies to local market needs and conditions.Key Qualifications and Skills:Pharmacist License or Bachelor’s degree in Pharmacy or a related field.Proven track record in medical device sales and business development.Strong understanding of the healthcare and regulatory landscape for medical devices.Excellent presentation, negotiation, and communication skills.Demonstrated leadership skills with the ability to build and manage teams.Experience in managing country-level operations, including financial oversight and compliance."}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4378326237","title":"Business Development Manager Klauke System","company":"Emerson","location":"St Louis","remote":false,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"","description":"Job DescriptionNous recherchons un(e) Business Développement Manager (BDM) hautement motivé(e) et tourné(e) vers l’avenir afin de stimuler la croissance du Klauke System en France. Vous êtes responsable de l’identification, du développement et de la concrétisation de nouvelles opportunités business, avec un fort accent sur les tendances émergentes liées à la distribution d’énergie, à l’extension des réseaux et aux nouvelles sources d’énergie. Ce rôle requiert une connaissance approfondie du secteur, une forte agilité stratégique ainsi qu’une excellente capacité d’engagement et de développement des relations clients. Le poste est rattaché au Director Business Development Klauke System EMEA.Responsabilités du poste: Générer des ventes via des visites sur site, audits techniques et conseils techniques auprès de clients existants et prospects.  Développer les ventes par des démonstrations terrain, salons professionnels et événements de type roadshow.  Définir et exécuter un plan stratégique de business development pour le Klauke System en France.  Identifier, engager et développer des relations avec les parties prenantes clés (utilities, infrastructures énergétiques, EPC, intégrateurs systèmes, grands comptes).  Analyser les tendances de marché (distribution et transmission d’énergie, extension et modernisation des réseaux, data centers, énergies décentralisées, smart grids).  Positionner Klauke comme fournisseur de solutions de connexion électrique sûres, efficaces et orientées futur.  Assurer le suivi des leads, opportunités, offres, pipelines projets et performances des distributeurs.  Élaborer des plans de comptes, des prévisions de ventes et des plans d’affaires annuels (forecast mensuel et annuel).  Agir en tant qu’expert produit et application Klauke System, incluant la formation des distributeurs et des clients finaux. Qui êtes-vous :Vous concevez et déployez des solutions qui répondent aux attentes des clients. Vous vous tenez informé(e) des politiques, pratiques et tendances actuelles et futures, tant au sein de l’organisation que chez les concurrents et sur le marché. Vous faites preuve de persévérance pour atteindre vos objectifs, même face aux obstacles et aux difficultés. Vous savez construire et entretenir des réseaux solides, formels et informels.Qualifications et expérience requises : Formation technique ou commerciale, idéalement de niveau ingénieur (mécanique, électrotechnique ou équivalent).  Minimum 3 ans d’expérience réussie en vente terrain, gestion de comptes ou développement commercial, idéalement dans le secteur électrique ou des outils professionnels.  Bonne compréhension technique des équipements, outils et solutions électriques.  Maîtrise des outils informatiques et CRM.  Français courant et anglais professionnel requis.  Disponibilité pour des déplacements fréquents en France. Des qualifications qui font la différence : Expérience dans la vente de solutions techniques à forte valeur ajoutée.  Aisance dans les démonstrations produite et les présentations techniques.  Capacité à évoluer dans un environnement multiculturel et matriciel. Notre offreRejoindre Emerson Professional Tools, c’est intégrer un groupe international reconnu pour la qualité de ses produits et son expertise technique, offrant un environnement orienté performance, autonomie et développement professionnel.Intéressé(e) par ce poste de Business Development Manager Klauke System ? Rejoignez‑nous et participez activement au développement de nos solutions sur le marché français.About UsWHY EMERSONOur Commitment to Our PeopleAt Emerson, we are motivated by a spirit of collaboration that helps our diverse, multicultural teams across the world drive innovation that makes the world healthier, safer, smarter, and more sustainable. And we want you to join us in our bold aspiration.We have built an engaged community of inquisitive, dedicated people who thrive knowing they are welcomed, trusted, celebrated, and empowered to solve the world’s most complex problems — for our customers, our communities, and the planet. You’ll contribute to this vital work while further developing your skills through our award-winning employee development programs. We are a proud corporate citizen in every city where we operate and are committed to our people, our communities, and the world at large. We take this responsibility seriously and strive to make a positive impact through every endeavor.At Emerson, you’ll see firsthand that our people are at the center of everything we do. So, let’s go. Let’s think differently. Learn, collaborate, and grow. Seek opportunity. Push boundaries. Be empowered to make things better. Speed up to break through. Let’s go, together.Accessibility Assistance or AccommodationIf you have a disability and are having difficulty accessing or using this website to apply for a position, please contact: idisability.administrator@emerson.com .About EmersonEmerson is a global leader in automation technology and software. Through our deep domain expertise and legacy of flawless execution, Emerson helps customers in critical industries like life sciences, energy, power and renewables, chemical and advanced factory automation operate more sustainably while improving productivity, energy security and reliability.With global operations and a comprehensive portfolio of software and technology, we are helping companies implement digital transformation to measurably improve their operations, conserve valuable resources and enhance their safety.We offer equitable opportunities, celebrate diversity, and embrace challenges with confidence that, together, we can make an impact across a broad spectrum of countries and industries. Whether you’re an established professional looking for a career change, an undergraduate student exploring possibilities, or a recent graduate with an advanced degree, you’ll find your chance to make a difference with Emerson. Join our team – let’s go!No calls or agencies please."}
