ls Ability to follow written instructions carefully Detail-oriented mindset with strong organizational habits Comfortable performing repetitive administrative tasks with consistency Ability to work independently in a remote, work-from-home environment Reliable high-speed internet connection Access to a computer suitable for remote administrative work Entry-level candidates welcome — training and onboarding support provided.No advanced technical background required. This role focuses on reliability, structure, and accuracy.Work DetailsLocation: Fully Remote / Work From HomeRegion Supported: MENA (UAE, Qatar, Saudi Arabia)Schedule: Flexible scheduling windows with consistent availability requiredHours: Full-time or part-time depending on workload and project scopeCompensation: Based on experience and engagement levelIdeal Candidate ProfileThis Position Is Ideal For Individuals Who:Are beginning a career in administration, operations support, or remote coordination Prefer structured, process-driven environments Take pride in clean spreadsheets and organized systems Enjoy improving workflow clarity Thrive on consistency and predictable responsibilities Want a long-term remote administrative career path Growth &amp; Career DevelopmentThis Role Provides Hands-on Exposure To:Remote operations management Administrative workflow coordination Data management systems Task tracking platforms Internal reporting structures Process documentation standards Strong Performance May Lead To Advancement Opportunities Such As:Senior Administrative Assistant Operations Coordinator Quality Assurance Support Specialist Workflow Analyst Team Lead Operations Supervisor We prioritize internal growth and structured skill development. Reliable team members who demonstrate consistency, initiative, and ownership will have clear opportunities for progression.Why Join Us?100% remote opportunity Entry-level friendly with training provided Clear performance expectations Structured workflows and guidance Growth-focused operational environment Exposure to regional operations in UAE, Qatar, and Saudi Arabia Long-term career development potential If you are detail-driven, organized, and looking for a stable remote administrative opportunity with long-term growth potential, we encourage you to apply.Desired Skills And ExperienceEntry-Level Administrative Assistant, Remote Operations Support, Work From Home Jobs, Data Entry, Remote Jobs UAE, Remote Jobs Saudi Arabia"}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4374296317","title":"Entry-Level Remote Operations & Office Support","company":"PulseMediaNL (APAC REGION)","location":"Madrid","remote":false,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"","description":"Position OverviewWe are seeking a motivated and detail-oriented Entry-Level Administrative Assistant to support remote operational activities across teams serving the MENA region and broader markets, including the UAE, Qatar, and Saudi Arabia. This fully remote opportunity is ideal for individuals who thrive in structured environments, value organization, and are comfortable managing responsibilities independently while maintaining high standards of accuracy.In this role, you will contribute directly to the efficiency of daily business operations by ensuring administrative systems remain organized, updated, and aligned with established internal procedures. Your work will support cross-regional coordination by maintaining accurate records, tracking workflows, and preserving documentation standards. Strong organizational habits, consistency, and reliability are essential for success.This position is well suited for candidates beginning their professional journey in administrative support, remote coordination, or operational assistance. Prior experience is welcomed but not required. Comprehensive onboarding and clear process documentation will be provided to ensure you understand expectations, tools, and workflow standards. Success in this role depends primarily on dependability, attention to detail, and the ability to carefully follow structured procedures.Primary ResponsibilitiesAdministrative Record MaintenanceYou will manage and update structured administrative records that support reporting and internal operations. This includes working daily with spreadsheets in Google Sheets or Microsoft Excel, reviewing entries for completeness and formatting consistency, and correcting obvious discrepancies. Standardizing naming conventions, regional identifiers, and folder structures will be part of your routine responsibilities. You will also identify missing or unclear data and flag it appropriately for follow-up. Maintaining clean, accurate datasets is critical to supporting reliable reporting and operational decision-making.Workflow Coordination SupportYou will assist in organizing incoming requests and ensuring tasks are properly categorized within established internal systems. Responsibilities include routing assignments to appropriate team members, tracking task progress, and following up on incomplete or delayed items. Clear written communication will be necessary when clarifying instructions or requesting additional information. Your coordination efforts will help maintain transparency and accountability across distributed teams.Operational Tracking and ReportingMaintaining accurate trackers that reflect ongoing, completed, and pending work will be part of your daily workflow. You will log updates, document issues, and record items requiring further attention. Periodically, you may prepare brief summaries outlining task progress and outstanding items. Identifying recurring data inconsistencies or workflow inefficiencies and escalating them appropriately will contribute to continuous operational improvement.Scheduling and Administrative CoordinationWhen required, you will provide light coordination support such as updating shared calendars, confirming availability, sending deadline reminders, and tracking onboarding steps or project milestones. Ensuring administrative timelines move forward smoothly will require careful organization and consistent follow-through.Documentation and Quality StandardsA core component of this role is maintaining documentation integrity. You will review your work prior to submission to ensure alignment with internal formatting standards and procedural guidelines. Keeping shared folders organized and ensuring documentation remains accessible and consistently structured will help preserve operational efficiency. Adherence to standard operating procedures is expected at all times.Performance ExpectationsSuccessful candidates demonstrate high accuracy with minimal errors, steady daily productivity, and dependable task completion. You should be comfortable working independently in a remote setting while maintaining accountability. Clear written communication when encountering obstacles is essential. The ability to execute repetitive administrative processes with precision and consistency is critical to long-term success in this role.QualificationsBasic proficiency in Google Sheets or Microsoft Excel Strong written communication skills High attention to detail and organizational discipline Ability to carefully follow structured written instructions Comfortable working independently in a remote environment Reliable internet connection and appropriate home workspace setup This is an entry-level role, and structured training will be provided.Work StructureThis is a fully remote position supporting regional teams across the MENA region, including the UAE, Qatar, and Saudi Arabia. Flexible scheduling options may be available; however, consistency and reliability are required. Both full-time and part-time arrangements may be considered based on operational needs.Growth OpportunitiesThis role provides hands-on exposure to administrative systems, workflow coordination, operational tracking, and remote collaboration. High-performing team members may progress into advanced positions such as Senior Administrative Assistant, Operations Coordinator, Quality Support Specialist, Workflow Analyst, Team Lead, or Operations Supervisor. We prioritize internal development and recognize individuals who demonstrate initiative, consistency, and strong organizational capabilities.Ideal CandidateYou prefer structured environments and take pride in maintaining organized systems. You enjoy working with data, tracking progress, and ensuring tasks are completed accurately and on schedule. You value reliability and contribute effectively behind the scenes to enhance team efficiency. If you are seeking a long-term remote administrative career path with advancement potential, this role offers a strong foundation.Core SkillsEntry-Level Administrative Assistant, Remote Operations Support, Work-from-Home Administrative Role, Data Entry, Spreadsheet Management, Task Tracking, Workflow Coordination, Business Operations Support, Virtual Administrative Assistant, Remote Entry-Level OpportunityIf you are dependable, detail-oriented, and eager to build a career in remote administrative operations, we encourage you to apply."}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4375933272","title":"Executive-Level Interim AI Experts — Multiple Specialist Roles (GCC, Hybrid/Remote)","company":"Perform by AI","location":"Dubai","remote":false,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"","description":"Executive-Level Interim AI Experts — Multiple Specialist Roles (GCC, Hybrid/Remote)A well-established integrated solutions provider based in Saudi Arabia — backed by one of the Kingdom's leading conglomerates — is expanding its AI capabilities and offerings across consulting, digital solutions, training, and technology services. The company serves both healthcare and non-healthcare sectors and has delivered national-scale programmes for government entities across the Kingdom.The client is reviewing portfolios of executive-level interim experts across five specialist areas. If they decide to proceed, the intention is a multi-year engagement covering project delivery, internal capability building, and ongoing advisory support.Commitment: Part-time, 3 to 4 days per week Start Date: Expected before Q3 2026 Duration: Multi-year engagement anticipated Location: GCC (Saudi Arabia and UAE primarily). Depending on the nature of the engagement, on-site presence or hybrid delivery may be required. Some opportunities are expected to require remote support only.—MUST-HAVE REQUIREMENTS (ALL ROLES)Must be legally eligible to work as an independent consultant. Applications that do not confirm this will not be considered.Executive-Level Consulting Experience: Must have held executive-level roles (Partner, Director, or equivalent) within a consulting, advisory, or professional services firm. Evidence of leading large-scale AI engagements at this level is essential.Experience: Minimum 15 years of professional experience, with at least 5 years of direct AI-related experience at executive level.Education: Postgraduate or Doctoral degree (PhD or equivalent) in Artificial Intelligence, Computer Science, or a related discipline.Sector Experience: Multi-sector experience required. Healthcare, government, and digital solutions sectors are of particular relevance.Geographic Experience: EU or US experience required. GCC / Middle East experience preferred.Languages: English required. Arabic as a second language is preferred.—FIVE INTERIM EXPERT ROLESPlease indicate which role(s) you are applying for when you submit your profile.—Role 1 — Smart Cities AI Expert (Interim)Senior expert in AI applications for smart city environments — with hands-on experience across command centres, urban digital twins, IoT-driven urban analytics, intelligent transport and mobility, energy and utilities optimisation, public safety, and AI-powered citizen services.You will help the client develop and strengthen their smart city AI offerings — designing new AI-enabled service lines, integrating AI into existing capabilities, and building referenceable frameworks for smart city AI delivery. You will also provide senior subject matter expertise on live engagements including digital twin deployment, sensor-driven decision support, predictive infrastructure management, and real-time operational intelligence for city-scale systems.—Role 2 — AI Governance &amp; Risk Expert (Interim)Senior expert in enterprise AI governance, risk management, and regulatory compliance — with deep working knowledge of the EU AI Act (including high-risk AI system requirements entering enforcement in August 2026), and ideally the Saudi SDAIA AI Ethics Principles, AI Adoption Framework, PDPL, and ISO 42001.You will help the client build internal AI governance capabilities and advisory offerings — designing governance frameworks, responsible AI policies, risk classification methodologies, and compliance operating models for their end clients. You will also provide senior expertise on AI risk assessments, regulatory compliance programmes, AI audit and assurance frameworks, and enterprise-wide governance structures.—Role 3 — AI Strategy &amp; Readiness Expert (Interim)Senior expert in enterprise AI strategy development and organisational readiness — with experience leading AI maturity assessments, use case identification and prioritisation, AI roadmap development, business case design, and AI operating models for enterprise-wide adoption.You will help the client build repeatable AI strategy and readiness advisory capabilities — designing assessment methodologies, maturity frameworks, roadmap templates, and operating model blueprints for their client base. You will also provide senior expertise on live engagements, advising C-suite and board-level stakeholders on AI adoption decisions, investment plans, and use case prioritisation.—Role 4 — AI Academy &amp; Leadership Capability Building Expert (Interim)Senior expert in the design, development, and delivery of executive-level AI leadership programmes and corporate learning academies. You will support the creation of an AI Academy targeted at director-level leaders and above. Experience managing academic and training partner ecosystems is highly valued.You will help design and establish the academy — including curriculum framework, learning module design, delivery model architecture (virtual, in-person, blended), programme governance, and integration of academic partnerships. You will also deliver executive-level AI capability building — facilitating C-suite workshops, developing leadership content across AI strategy, governance, risk, and responsible AI, and advising on workforce transformation and change management.—Role 5 — Digital Productisation Expert (Interim)Senior expert in the strategic productisation of professional services and enterprise solutions at scale. This is a strategic and commercial leadership role — not a technical development role. The ideal candidate has led multiple enterprise-scale productisation programmes, transitioning organisations from project-based delivery to product-led business models.You will assess existing consulting, digital, and training service lines, identify productisation opportunities, and design the roadmap for scalable, packaged offerings — including commercial models, pricing, and go-to-market strategies. You will also lead operating model transformation to support a product-led business, including the role of AI in enabling automation and scalability.—HOW TO APPLYSubmit your CV and clearly indicate which of the five roles you are applying for. If you are qualified for more than one, indicate all that apply. Shortlisted candidates will receive full client and project details."}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4357515719","title":"Field Service Specialist","company":"CoolIT Systems","location":"Calgary","remote":false,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"","description":"About CoolIT Systems Inc.Founded in Calgary, Alberta in 2001, CoolIT Systems is the leading Direct Liquid Cooling technology provider for data centers, supercomputers, and desktop computers. We design and manufacture solutions used by the largest tech companies globally.Recognized as one of “The Americas’ Fastest Growing Companies 2023” by Financial Times and honored with the Deloitte Fast 50 Clean Technology award in 2022, as well as the Deloitte Fast 500 distinction in both 2021 and 2022, CoolIT's rapid growth is capturing global attention.As demand for generative AI, high performance computing and cloud solutions rapidly expands, there has never been a more exciting time to join our team.RoleWhat You’ll DoWe’re looking for a skilled and motivated Field Service Specialist to support our global customer base. In this role, you’ll take the lead on deployments, maintenance, and field support for CoolIT’s cutting-edge cooling solutions, ensuring every project meets the highest standards of quality and industry best practices. Reporting to the Manager of Field Service Operations, you’ll gain hands-on experience with innovative technology while making a meaningful impact on customers worldwide.ResponsibilitiesPerform on-site and remote installations of CoolIT products. Conduct preventative and corrective maintenance on Direct Liquid Cooling (DLC) solutions. Assemble and prepare off-site spools and piping equipment. Interpret and work from technical blueprints. Provide remote technical support to on-site service specialists and end-users. Offer plumbing and HVAC consultation to internal team members and serve as a subject matter expert for field-related inquiries. Develop in-depth knowledge of CoolIT’s unique product line. Deliver in-person and remote training sessions for customers, technicians, and colleagues. Follow Professional Services processes to troubleshoot, mitigate, and resolve issues on-site, leveraging CoolIT’s Authorized Service Providers when necessary. Ensure compliance with all internal and external requirements, including environmental, health, and safety standards. Complete detailed service reports, system testing documentation, and other service-related paperwork in accordance with Professional Services procedures. Coordinate and dispatch on-site service visits with end-users and Authorized Service Providers. Who You AreBasic QualificationsMinimum 5 years of experience as a Service Specialist or in a similar technical role. Professional demeanor combined with strong hands-on technical skills. Experience in mission-critical environments preferred. Demonstrated ownership and accountability for delivering high-quality work. Adaptable and flexible, comfortable with evolving responsibilities as the company grows. Proficiency in Microsoft Office applications. Ability to travel internationally and meet all security clearance requirements. Valid driver’s license with a clean driving record. Physical capability to perform frequent heavy lifting (up to 150 lbs with assistance). Ability to work independently, including managing critical service calls confidently. Strong remote support and virtual troubleshooting skills to assist on-site technicians. Willingness to travel up to 50% as required. Preferred QualificationsStrong communication and presentation skills, with the ability to deliver clear, engaging training sessions and provide concise reporting to customers. Hands-on experience with pipe installation and joining, utilizing appropriate methods for various pipe materials. Foundational electrical knowledge, including the ability to understand control systems and a willingness to learn advanced system logic. Familiarity with hydronic heating and cooling systems, with practical knowledge of their components and operation. Skills