sition is immediately available and requires entering into an independent contractor agreement with Crossover as a Contractor of Record. The compensation level for this role is $50 USD/hour, which equates to $100,000 USD/year assuming 40 hours per week and 50 weeks per year. The payment period is weekly. Consult www.crossover.com/help-and-faqs for more details on this topic.Crossover Job Code: LJ-5266-AE-Dubai-HeadofSales.006"}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4374248772","title":"Individual Consultant - Data Manager - Data Integration & Analysis Department","company":"World Organisation for Animal Health","location":"Paris","remote":false,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"","description":"As an Organisation, WOAH collects, analyses, validates, and disseminates a large volume of information through different sources, platforms and processes to achieve its mandate.The importance of data and improving data-set value is paramount to policy-making at national and international levels. Policy-makers must rapidly create and coordinate actions based on complex information to positively impact the global animal health system and global health security. This is why WOAH strives to provide its Members and partners with robust information to strengthen animal health institutions and partnerships.The Data Integration &amp; Analytics Department (DIAD) leads the data management and data analytics efforts of the organisationUnder the authority of the WOAH’s Deputy Director General (International Standards and Science), and the direct supervision of the Head of the Data Integration &amp; Analytics Department (DIAD).The Data Manager will support the population of a modern and efficient cloud-based data warehouse containing the main scientific data assets of the organisation. The Data Manager will support the formatting, cleaning, quality checking, analysis, and interpretation (at national, regional and global levels) of diverse and varied data collected by WOAH.*Support the population and maintenance of WOAH cloud-based data warehouseIngest, clean, standardise, and validate diverse WOAH datasets in line with WOAH data management protocols (data cleaning, QA, harmonisation)Structure and formally document data pipelines ensuring traceability, reproducibility, and compliance with official statistical principles and WOAH standardsCoordinate with data owners across WOAH to ensure timely updates, resolve data inconsistencies, and maintain robust metadata documentation*Strengthen data integration across WOAH systems and processesMap, align, and integrate datasets across internal platforms (e.g., WAHIS, Animuse) and external source of data, improving coherence and interoperabilityDevelop and maintain data dictionaries, schemas, and controlled vocabularies to ensure consistencyCollaborate with Digital Transformation and Information System department and technical teams to troubleshoot integration issues and refine system-to-system dataflowsContribute to other activities of the Data Integration Department as required.Required qualifications and experience• A university degree in data science, statistics, or equivalent;• 1 to 3 years of working experience, with at least 1 year of direct experience in data management, data visualisation and data analysis;• Training and experience in writing and executing of scripts/queries utilising programming languages, such as R or Python.Additional experience (asset)• Experience in project management• Experience with MS Fabric• Experience relevant to animal health and/or public health• Experience working with multilateral frameworks and intergovernmental institutions• Professional experience gained in multicultural working environments, working with government, civil society, international organisations or relevant private sector entities.Technical skills:• Sound knowledge of data management and statistical principles, methods and processes (cleaning diverse data sets, performing data analyses, support data interpretation, and visualizing outputs);• Advanced proficiency in programming languages such as R, Python and good working knowledge of SQL• Concrete experience clearly articulating and presenting quantitative findings withhigh impact;• Ability to identify trends, to provide insight, and to offer expertise on how to achieve goals using data;• Excellent command of English, both written and oral;• Knowledge of another of the WOAH official languages (French or Spanish) is an asset;• Demonstrates commanding knowledge of, and ability to work across multiple project management systems, accompanied by knowledge in PowerPoint, Word, Excel, SharePoint, Power BI (or equivalent) and other web-based software applications.Interpersonal skills:• Highly self-motivated, ability to work independently, and keen on learning anddevelopment;• Ability to establish and maintain excellent working relationships in a multinational and multicultural environment.• Ability to effectively communicate complex data and ideas to non-expert audiences;• Proactive problem-solver skilled in leading partners toward creative and flexible solutions.• Organisational skills and demonstrated capacity to meet deadlines;• Coordination skills• Commitment to fostering a positive and supportive work environment amongst all team members with demonstrated ability to act as liaison across matrixed teams and organisations.• Ability to work in a multi-disciplinary team in an international environment.• Highly detail orientated, as well as capacity to see the global picture;• Flexible and dynamic personality, inspiring trust;• Team player who can integrate well into the department and is willing to commit to supporting the development of its outputs.Working conditions• Salary: 4000 – 5000 € / month depending on qualification and experience• Duration: 6 months• Start Date: as soon as possible• Location: Activities under this position may be carried out entirely remotelyGeneral informationWOAH places high value on a multicultural and positivework environment.WOAH is an equal opportunity employer and welcomes all qualified candidates, irrespective of their origin, gender, opinions or beliefs.If you are interested in the position, please complete your application online at the latest by March 16th, 2026."}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4375271606","title":"International Legal Counsel","company":"Randstad Enterprise","location":"Amsterdam","remote":false,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"","description":"Randstad Enterprise Group provides a wide range of HR and recruitment solutions designed to help companies grow, implement strategies, and improve business agility. With expertise spanning the entire talent spectrum, including talent acquisition and outplacement, our offerings include Managed Services Provider (RCS, MSP, SOW) programs, Recruitment Process Outsourcing (RPO), professional services, and career transition services, all supported by innovative technologies.This includes the development and creation of a temporary staffing relationship management tool in France: E-FLEX, a temporary work management platform.This role is fully remote within France. While candidates across France are welcome, our preference is for Paris-based individuals due to the location of our legal entities. Candidates outside of France with deep expertise in the French legal system will also be considered.Job purposeThe International Legal Counsel provides expert legal and contractual support to Randstad Enterprise Group, focusing primarily on the French market. This role serves as the dedicated in-house counsel for the E-FLEX platform, manages the end-to-end lifecycle of national and multinational client contracts, and ensures corporate compliance across procurement, data protection, and information security.This role is fully remote within France. While candidates across France are welcome, our preference is for Paris-based individuals due to the location of our legal entities. Candidates outside of France with deep expertise in the French legal system will also be considered.What you will do in this position:Manage and negotiate local and international client contracts, specifically focusing on service schedules, SLAs, and fee structures.Advise on legal and commercial risk decisions within contracts by providing clear options and strategic recommendations to stakeholders.Oversee contract interpretation and handle operational inquiries for all active accounts within France and abroad.Lead international negotiations and manage internal approval processes, including the preparation of management summaries regarding contractual risks.Supervise procurement activities and provide advice to the Enterprise Procurement Team on local legislative requirements.Manage data protection compliance and privacy notices, including GDPR requirements, OneTrust assessments, and the Register of Processing in connection with E-FLEX.Develop a specialized area of law within the team, such as employment law or licensing, to serve as a subject matter expert.Maintain a repository of legal templates and supporting documentation to ensure consistent performance expectations.Support the Enterprise Privacy and Information Security teams on local issues and maintain compliance with information barriers and competition laws.Provide regular training to operational teams and assist with the translation and implementation of global policies.What we ask from you:Provide a qualified legal background with 3–5 years of post-qualification experience in commercial and contract law, supported by specific, verifiable references.Deliver specialized international administrative support and lead contract negotiations for local, regional, and global commercial clients.Apply a working knowledge of employment law and staffing services to provide daily operational legal advice to internal account teams.Maintain a mandatory minimum level of experience working within the French legal system to advise on local issues independently.Act as the primary legal point of contact for French operations while working autonomously from a remote location in France or nearby regions.Demonstrate fluency in French and professional proficiency in English to draft and negotiate complex legal documents confidently.Use prior international exposure to collaborate effectively with a diverse European legal team and various local counsels.Develop a deep understanding of commercial business acumen, including the ability to challenge pricing and recognize potential tax matters.Balance legal perfection with business speed to meet the fast-paced operational needs of a sales-led organization.Exhibit a high level of dedication and autonomy to organize your own schedule while proactively challenging the status quo to protect company interests.What we can offer for you:We offer an inspiring working environment where you and your colleagues will make a tangible difference for our customers every day. You will have the opportunity to build an amazing career within a world-leading organization that sits at the forefront of the recruitment industry. To ensure your success, we provide a stimulating and supportive atmosphere that prioritizes your continuous professional development. We actively encourage you to develop a specialist area of law to deepen your expertise and elevate your standing within the legal community. You will be backed by the collective intelligence of the legal teams in Enterprise and Groupe Randstad France, ensuring you always have support for complex technical matters. Our team embraces modern efficiency, utilizing forward-thinking technology like Gemini to assist with sophisticated documentation and translation tasks. Beyond professional growth, we provide an attractive salary supplemented by a thorough and competitive benefits package. what next?If you are excited by this opportunity and would like to hear more, please contact Madani Toure madani.toure@randstadsourceright.pl"}
