cellence.Foster a positive, inclusive, and collaborative team culture aligned with company values.Conduct regular performance reviews and provide ongoing feedback and coaching.Support onboarding, and development initiatives for regional talent.Operational &amp; Business ManagementOversee daily B2B operations across the region to ensure efficiency, consistency, and compliance with organizational policies.Analyze business performance, identify gaps, and implement strategies for continuous improvement.Develop and execute regional action plans to exceed KPIs and business objectives.Ensure all operational processes are followed and consistently improved where needed.Stakeholder &amp; Relationship ManagementBuild strong relationships with key internal and external stakeholders, representing the region with professionalism and credibility.Collaborate closely with cross-functional teams to ensure alignment and smooth execution of initiatives.Act as the primary escalation point for the region, providing clear communication and timely solutions.Financial &amp; Performance OversightManage regional budgets, forecasts, and financial targets responsibly.Monitor key performance metrics and deliver monthly reporting to senior leadership.Identify opportunities for revenue growth and cost optimization within the region.Strategic Planning &amp; ExecutionProvide input on regional strategy based on market conditions, customer insights, and performance data.Lead the implementation of new projects, processes, and initiatives across the region.Support change management activities and ensure successful rollouts of new programs.Required Skills and ExperienceEssential Qualifications &amp; ExperienceProven experience in a Regional Manager or multi-site leadership role.Strong background in operations, business management, or people leadership.Demonstrated success in developing teams and achieving performance targets.Experience managing budgets, KPIs, and regional reporting.Skills &amp; CompetenciesExceptional leadership and interpersonal skills with the ability to inspire and motivate.Strong analytical and problem‑solving abilities, using data to drive decisions specifically in the Travel Tech B2B space.Excellent communication skills, both verbal and written.High level of organizational and time‑management skills.Ability to navigate ambiguity, manage multiple priorities, and deliver under pressure.Proactive mindset with strong ownership, accountability, and strategic thinking.Advanced French and English is a must.Preferred ExperienceExperience working in a fast‑paced, multi-country or international environment.Familiarity with cross-functional collaboration structures and remote team leadership.Proven ability to influence stakeholders at all levels.At HBX Group, we believe that diversity drives innovation and makes travel a force for good. We're committed to creating an inclusive workplace where everyone feels valued and respected, embracing different backgrounds, perspectives and talents. Join us and be part of a team where diversity and equal opportunities really do make a difference."}
