{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4379595710","title":"Sales Executive (Outbound Sales)","company":"Altery","location":"London","remote":false,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"","description":"About UsAre you passionate about FinTech and ready to make a tangible impact in a dynamic company where your decisions shape the future? Altery could be the next chapter in your professional journey!We’re expanding rapidly and looking for an experienced  Sales Executive to help grow our international client base. In this role, you’ll lead high-impact sales initiatives that drive revenue growth and strengthen our presence in global markets. You’ll own the entire sales cycle – from strategising and prospecting to negotiating and closing complex B2B deals across diverse industries. To succeed in this role, you will need 7+ years of experience in fast-paced B2B sales or business development, with at least 2–3 years focused on selling financial services and payments products.This is a remote role, but you’ll need to be based in the EMEA region.What you’ll be doingDrive outbound sales into new regions and market segments using your own networks and executing global targeted outreach strategies in line with Altery’s go-to-market plan.Own the end-to-end business development &amp; sales cycle – from prospecting and pitching to negotiating and closing – using a mix of outreach channels including cold calls, networking, email, social media, and industry events.Manage the entire outbound sales process from first contact to close, with a focus on B2B international companies and entrepreneurs.Build and maintain a strong sales pipeline, converting high-potential prospects into active Altery customers.Collaborate with the Customer Success team to ensure continued engagement and long-term growth of the customers you bring on board.Identify and develop relationships with strategic partners across various industries.Keep detailed records of your activity and pipeline progress in our CRM (HubSpot), ensuring a high level of sales hygiene and pipeline visibility.Share on-the-ground insights to help shape product, positioning, and go-to-market strategy.Work cross-functionally with the broader GTM team to continuously improve targeting, outreach tactics, and messaging.What you'll bring3+ years of experience in sales or business development within a fast-paced B2B environment, ideally in the financial services or payments sector.At least 2-3 years of experience selling financial services and payments products; preferably Virtual IBANs, FX, and cross-border payments. Proven track record of meeting and exceeding sales targets, with strong outbound sales experience and a commercial mindset.Experience working across global markets and managing high-volume sales, particularly in international SMB/SME segments.Strong negotiation and consultative sales skills, with proven ability in pitching and prospecting clients. Ability to evaluate and qualify clients based on their potential future profitability.Fluent in English; proficiency in Italian or French will be considered a strong advantage.Knowledge and sales experience in one or more of our key industries, including but not limited to: Wholesale, Cryptocurrencies &amp; Digital Assets, Marketing &amp; Advertising, Affiliate, E-commerce Platforms and Marketplaces: Retail and Digital goods, Logistics, IT &amp; Software development, Financial institutions, Gaming &amp; Digital product distribution, Online services.What we offerTeam and our Product: We are team players and we are passionate about our product and understand what we aim to achieve and the impact it will make.Growth Opportunities: You can Influence and shape our story while advancing your career.Flexibility: We always listen to our people and can be flexible with arrangements.Hybrid Working: We don't expect you to be in the office every day.Local Market Perks: Enjoy insurance coverage, local perks, and beautiful offices.Why to join usWe may not be perfect, but our strength lies in our resilience. Facing challenges with our expertise, positive attitude, and a supportive environment where everyone relies on one another gives us confidence in what we do. We empower our people to make decisions, explore, and experiment — micromanagement isn’t our style. We reward those who take on additional responsibilities and go the extra mile.We are proud of how diverse and unique we are. We thrive on diverse views, love learning from one another, and believe that our differences fuel our curiosity"}
